### About Design Video Interfaces
This site has Designing Video Interfaces
  
#### Further Reading
  

* Seidel, Niels (accepted). Interaction design pattern for spatio-temporal annotations in video learning environments. In Proceedings of the 20th European Conference on Pattern Languages of Programs. ACM.

* Seidel, Niels (accepted). Making web video accessible - interaction design patterns for accessible e-learning technologies. In Proceedings of the 20th European Conference on Pattern Languages of Programs (p. [accepted]). ACM.

*  Seidel, Niels (2014). *Interaction design patterns for design and development of video learning environments.* In Proceedings of the 19th European Conference on Pattern Languages of Programs (p. [in print]). New York, NY, USA: ACM. doi:http://dx.doi.org/10.1145/2721956.2721981

*  Seidel, Niels (2014). *Interaction design patterns for interactive video players in video-based learning environments.* In Proceedings of the 19th European Conference on Pattern Languages of Programs (p. [in print]). New York, NY, USA: ACM. doi:http://dx.doi.org/10.1145/2721956.2721980

    
#### Related Pattern Languages
* Jeniffer Tidwell (2011). Designing Interfaces - Patterns for Effective Interaction Design (2nd ed.). Sebastopol: O’Reilly Media. [website](http://www.designinginterfaces.com/)

*  Martijn van Welie & Gerit C. van der Veer (2003). *Pattern Languages in Interaction Design: Structure and Organization.* In M. Rauterberg (Ed.), Proceedings of Interact ’03, 1-5 September (pp. 527–534). Amsterdam: IOS Press. [Website](http://www.welie.com/ patterns/)

*  Tibor Kunert (2009). User-Centered Interaction Design Patterns for Interactive Digital Televison Applications. Dordrecht / Heidelberg / London / New York: Springer.

*  Christian Crumlish & Erin Malone (2009). Designing Social Interfaces. (M. Treseler, Ed.). Sebastopol: O’Reilly Media. [Website](http://designingsocialinterfaces.com)

*  Yahoo!, *ypatterns*. [Website](http://developer.yahoo.com/ypatterns/)

*  Douglas K. van Duyne, James A. Landay, & Jason I. Hong (2006). *The Design of Sites: Patterns for Creating Winning Web Sites* (2nd edition.). Prentice Hall.
 
  
  
